CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 17 reads: "Strategy - Lain Lee, Democratic candidate for alderman in the Fifth Ward, and his running mate, Silas Knox, candidate for constable, exchange ideas for Tuesday's strategy. This team provided color and a constant all-day appeal for votes from one or more sound trucks.  They had everything but "inside organization" - and lost. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Lain Lee, Silas Knox, and unknown man gathered around car door with posters that read "Alderman Vote For Lain L. Lee X" and "Lee... 17, 1955," during 1955 primary elections
